        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 2:40PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 240 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Baywood, or near Fries, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Airy...
Galax...
Hillsville...
Independence...
Fries...
Fancy Gap...
and Ennice.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
